                    <lb n="3" break="no"/>σ<hi rend="ligature">ου</hi> ζήσαντος ἔ<hi rend="ligature">τη</hi> <num value="10">ι</num> <expan><abbr>κ</abbr><ex>αὶ</ex></expan> Νικήτα ζήσαντος ἔ<hi rend="ligature">τη</hi> <num value="8">η</num>
                    <lb n="4"/>τούτων <hi rend="ligature">μνή</hi>σθητι <expan><abbr><hi rend="supraline">Κ</hi></abbr><ex>ύρι</ex><abbr><hi rend="supraline">ε</hi></abbr></expan> ἐν <hi rend="ligature">τῇ</hi> βασιλείᾳ σου
                    <lb n="5"/>Ἐτελειώθησαν <expan><abbr>μ</abbr><ex>ηνὶ</ex></expan> Δεκε<hi rend="ligature">μβ</hi>ρίῳ <num value="27">κζ</num>
                    <lb n="6"/><expan><abbr>Ἰν<hi rend="intraline">δ</hi></abbr><ex>ικτιῶνος</ex></expan> <num value="6">ἕκ<hi rend="ligature">τη</hi>ς</num> <g ref="#palm">⸙</g>
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp><app><note>Text after Manganaro 2001, with ligatures added</note></app></listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP">
                <p>Tomb of those lying in God at rest, of Constantine, who lived 12 years, of Mellosos, who lived 10 years and of Niketas who lived 8 years. Remember these in your kingdom, O Lord! They died in the month of December on the 27th (day), in the 6th Indiction.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="it" resp="Manganaro">
                <p>Tomba dei giacenti in Dio qui in pace, di Costantino vissuto anni dodici, di Melloso vissuto anni dieci e di Niceta vissuto anni otto. Di questi ricordati, o Signore, nel tuo regno! Morirono nel mese di dicesmbre (il giorno) ventisette. della indizione sesta.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p><!--commented out pending revision-->
                    <!--epitaph of Konstantinos, Mellosos and Niketas; rectangular white marble plaque, found 1960 and built into a wall of the sacristy of the cathedral. Rocco is the ed. pr. Many ligatures; letter forms suggested C4-5 AD date to Rocco; Brugnone prefers later b/c of absence of consular date in indiction; evidence of persistence of Doricisms in Sicily in the names. The three boys may be brothers?--></p>
            </div>
